.TH WHISRSD 1 "2026-03-14" "whisrs 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
whisrsd \- whisrs dictation daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B whisrsd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B whisrsd
is the background daemon for the whisrs dictation system. It manages audio
capture, transcription, window tracking, and text injection via a virtual
keyboard.
.PP
The daemon listens on a Unix domain socket for commands from the
.BR whisrs (1)
CLI client. It runs as a long-lived process, either standalone or as a
systemd user service.
.PP
On startup, the daemon:
.IP \(bu 2
Loads configuration from
.IR ~/.config/whisrs/config.toml
.IP \(bu 2
Checks /dev/uinput access for virtual keyboard
.IP \(bu 2
Checks for available audio input devices
.IP \(bu 2
Auto-detects the active window manager/compositor
.IP \(bu 2
Initializes the selected transcription backend
.IP \(bu 2
Binds the Unix domain socket and begins accepting commands
.SH STATE MACHINE
The daemon maintains one of three states:
.TP
.B idle
Waiting for a toggle command. No audio is being captured.
.TP
.B recording
Audio is being captured from the microphone. A second toggle or a cancel
command transitions out of this state.
.TP
.B transcribing
Audio has been sent to the transcription backend. The daemon is waiting
for results. Text is typed at the cursor as it becomes available.
.SH TRANSCRIPTION BACKENDS
.TP
.B groq
Groq Whisper API. Free tier available. Audio is chunked at silence
boundaries and sent as HTTP POST requests. Timestamp-based deduplication
prevents repeated text.
.TP
.B openai-realtime
OpenAI Realtime API via WebSocket. Provides true streaming transcription
with the lowest latency. Recommended for the best experience.
.TP
.B openai
OpenAI REST API. Simple HTTP POST, non-streaming fallback.
.TP
.B local
Local transcription via whisper.cpp (requires the
.B local
feature flag at compile time). Fully offline.
.SH SOCKET
The daemon creates a Unix domain socket at:
.PP
.RS
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/whisrs.sock
.RE
.PP
If
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
is not set, falls back to:
.PP
.RS
.IR /tmp/whisrs\-<uid>.sock
.RE
.PP
The protocol uses length-prefixed JSON messages (4-byte big-endian length
header followed by a JSON body).
.PP
On startup, the daemon checks for and removes stale sockets from previous
instances. If another daemon is already running, it exits with an error.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGINT
Graceful shutdown. The socket file is removed before exit.
.TP
.B SIGTERM
Graceful shutdown (when run as a systemd service).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Controls log verbosity. Examples:
.BR info ,
.BR debug ,
.BR "whisrs=debug" .
Default is
.BR info .
.TP
.B WHISRS_GROQ_API_KEY
Groq API key. Overrides the config file value.
.TP
.B WHISRS_OPENAI_API_KEY
OpenAI API key. Overrides the config file value.
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Socket directory.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Configuration directory.
.TP
.B WAYLAND_DISPLAY
Used to detect Wayland session for clipboard operations.
.TP
.B HYPRLAND_INSTANCE_SIGNATURE
Used to detect Hyprland compositor for window tracking.
.TP
.B SWAYSOCK
Used to detect Sway compositor for window tracking.
.TP
.B XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Used to detect X11 session for window tracking.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/whisrs/config.toml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/whisrs.sock
IPC socket.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/whisrs/recovery/
Audio recovery files saved on transcription failure.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run the daemon in the foreground with debug logging:
.PP
.RS
RUST_LOG=debug whisrsd
.RE
.PP
Run the daemon in the background:
.PP
.RS
whisrsd &
.RE
.PP
Enable as a systemd user service:
.PP
.RS
systemctl \-\-user enable \-\-now whisrs.service
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR whisrs (1)
